---
import PrincipleRow from '../ui/PrincipleRow.astro';
---

<section id="stack" class="stack-section" aria-labelledby="stack-heading">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="section-intro">
      <h2 id="stack-heading">How I choose a tech stack</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">Fast to ship, easy to hand off, boring where boring is correct.</p>
    </div>

    <dl class="principles-list">

      <PrincipleRow term="Static first">
        If the content doesn&rsquo;t need a server, I don&rsquo;t use one. Astro is my default —
        it ships zero JavaScript unless I ask it to. Fast page loads, zero cold starts, no attack
        surface from a running process.
      </PrincipleRow>

      <PrincipleRow term="Reach for the platform">
        Native <code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code>, CSS scroll-snap,
        <code>IntersectionObserver</code>. If the browser can do it, I don&rsquo;t reach for a
        dependency. Less to update, less to audit, less to explain to the next developer.
      </PrincipleRow>

      <PrincipleRow term="Add a framework when the UI earns it">
        React when the interaction complexity justifies the bundle cost — not by default.
        I&rsquo;ve shipped Astro with React islands for exactly two interactive pieces while
        everything else stayed zero-JS. That was the right call.
      </PrincipleRow>

      <PrincipleRow term="Accessibility is a constraint, not a checklist">
        WCAG 2.2 AA, keyboard navigation, visible focus styles, screen reader testing,
        <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> — these get considered at the design stage, not bolted
        on at the end. I love a good animation. The focus ring comes first.
      </PrincipleRow>

      <PrincipleRow term="I can work both sides of the API">
        Comfortable with Supabase, row-level security, OAuth flows, and writing endpoints — not
        just consuming them. TanStack Query when the frontend needs to cache and share that data.
        I&rsquo;m not a backend engineer by title, but I won&rsquo;t block on one for a fetch call.
      </PrincipleRow>

    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .stack-section {
    padding-block: var(--space-16);
  }

  .section-intro {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-8);
  }

  .section-lead {
    color: var(--tone-text-muted);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.2vw, 1.15rem);
    max-width: 64ch;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .principles-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  /* PrincipleRow hover is self-contained — no overrides needed here */
</style>
